S{Lips dry, cracked, painful or black.} S{Tongue burning and tingling, as if a thousand pins were sticking in it.} S{Tongue dry and chippy, parched and fissured.} S{Throat and tongue black, tender and ulcerated patches in inside of lips and cheeks.} S{Intensely bad smell from mouth.}


:rubric=9. Throat.
S{Prickling and burning in throat and oesophagus.} S{Heat rising up from the stomach.} S{Spasmodic contraction of oesophagus.} S{Inability to swallow.} S{Sore-throat worse on r. side.} S{Hawking of clear white mucus.} S{Fauces red and covered with a mucous exudation.} S{Uvula whitened and shrivelled.}


:rubric=11. Stomach.
S{Wants a drink of water every few minutes.} S{Constant belching up of wind.} S{Vomiting of drunkards.} S{Excessive nausea, and inclination to vomit; while eating a little, after breakfast.} S{Vomiting of: Bright's disease; sea-sickness; cancer; pregnancy.} S{Weight in epigastrium as if burdened with flatulence.} S{Burning in stomach.} S{Total loss of appetite.} S{Desire for whiskey.}


